<GUIClass name="CM_FilterTable" id="70979e1d-9831-445a-9d78-a14af2356535">
    <superclass name="CM_DataTable"/>
    <transient/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>

		Paint on a form, or use 'change type' to an existing CM_DataTable in painter. (retains all the methods)
		
		At initialisation of the table, call &lt;CM_FilterTable&gt;.columnFilterSetup( true )
		The "true" causes the build all of the controls used for the filtering. This should only be done once in
		the life of the form.
		
		The only other thing that is required is for the 'scroll' event method to be created with no code in it
		on the table ( this seems to be related to a Jade issue ).
		
		Call &lt;CM_FilterTable&gt;.applyColumnFilterToRow() to update a row at a time when notes need processing on your
		table.
		
		Call &lt;CM_FilterTable&gt;.doClearFilters( true ) to clear and rebuild available filter values after repopulating
		your table with new data.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="_usergui"/>
    <Constant name="MaxMatchLength" id="a82810b7-b630-45b8-82a7-4619f9f56bea">
        <source>60</source>
        <type name="Integer"/>
    </Constant>
